{
  "integrative": {
    "title": "Integrative Close: Hazardous Industrial Power",
    "objective": "Synthesize the selection of wiring systems with the operational requirements of a hazardous and industrial environment.",
    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "Hazardous environments involve risks like flammable vapors or explosive dust where a single spark could be catastrophic.",
      "Industrial settings require high mechanical protection for power circuits due to the presence of heavy machinery.",
      "Radial circuits are often used for dedicated supplies to heavy-duty equipment.",
      "Wiring systems like SWA (Steel Wire Armoured) or Steel Conduit provide the necessary physical barrier for these conditions."
    ],
    "questionText": "You are installing a radial power circuit for a heavy-duty extraction fan in a chemical processing plant (a hazardous and industrial environment). Justify the selection of a heavy-duty metallic wiring system—such as Steel Wire Armoured (SWA) cable or Steel Conduit—by explaining how its specific physical properties protect the circuit from the unique risks present in this environment.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "The metallic construction (armour or steel wall) provides high mechanical protection against impact from industrial machinery or moving equipment.",
      "The robust enclosure prevents internal electrical faults or sparks from escaping and igniting flammable vapors or dust in the hazardous atmosphere.",
      "The system maintains the integrity of the radial circuit by preventing physical damage that could lead to short circuits or fire in a high-risk area."
    ],
    "hint": "Think about how the 'armour' or 'steel pipe' protects the conductors from being crushed and how it contains electrical faults in a place where a spark could cause an explosion."
  }
}

